Hong Kong proposed a plastic bag tax. Supermarkets will offer customer incentives to lessen use. Japan proposes to stop retailers from giving out free plastic bags. Bangladesh bans production, distribution and marketing of polythene shopping bags and recommends strict enforcement of the law. India's state of Maharashtra banned manufacture, sale and use of plastic bags. The plastics manufacturing industry objects. France urged the public to spurn supermarket plastic bags. Taiwan banned businesses from giving free plastic bags but lifted the ban from bistros, which ignored it. China encourages supermarkets to voluntarily reduce plastic bag distribution and plans to prohibit it. 